Package org.forgerock.openam.saml2.audit

Interface SAML2EventLogger

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SAML2Auditor
    public interface SAML2EventLogger
    A SAML2EventLogger can receive information about SAML2 request progress and success along with information to track individual requests. Security critical information should not be passed to this class.

    • Method Detail

      • auditAccessAttempt

        void auditAccessAttempt()
        Publishes an audit event with details of the attempted SAML2 operation, if the 'access' topic is audited.
        Throws:
        org.forgerock.audit.AuditException - If an exception occurred that prevented the audit event from being published.

      • auditAccessSuccess

        void auditAccessSuccess()
        Publishes an event with details of the successfully completed SAML2 operation, if the 'access' topic is audited.

        Any exception that occurs while trying to publish the audit event will be captured in the debug logs but otherwise ignored.

      • auditAccessFailure

        void auditAccessFailure​(String errorCode,
                        String message)
        Publishes an event with details of the failed CREST operation, if the 'access' topic is audited.

        Any exception that occurs while trying to publish the audit event will be captured in the debug logs but otherwise ignored.

        Parameters:
        errorCode - A unique code that identifies the error condition.
        message - A human-readable description of the error that occurred.
